  "prompt": "What are some songs that make you cry?",
  "response": "Music has a profound ability to evoke emotions, and many songs are known for their ability to touch listeners deeply and even bring them to tears. Here's a list of some such emotionally powerful songs across various genres:\n\n1. **\"Tears in Heaven\" by Eric Clapton**\n   - Written after the tragic loss of his son, this heartfelt ballad delves into grief and longing.\n\n2. **\"Someone Like You\" by Adele**\n   - A poignant reflection on lost love and moving on, Adele's powerful vocals amplify the song's emotional depth.\n\n3. **\"Hallelujah\" by Leonard Cohen (and various covers)**\n   - This hauntingly beautiful song explores themes of love, loss, and redemption, resonating deeply with many listeners.\n\n4. **\"Fix You\" by Coldplay**\n   - A song about offering comfort and support during difficult times, its gradual build-up and soaring climax can be incredibly moving.\n\n5. **\"Everybody Hurts\" by R.E.M.**\n   - A reassuring message to those feeling down, emphasizing that they're not alone in their struggles.\n\n6. **\"The Night We Met\" by Lord Huron**\n   - A melancholic tune about longing and the desire to return to a past moment.\n\n7. **\"Skinny Love\" by Bon Iver (or Birdy\u2019s cover)**\n   - This song captures the fragility and complexities of a strained relationship.\n\n8. **\"Candle in the Wind\" by Elton John**\n   - Originally written in honor of Marilyn Monroe and later adapted for Princess Diana, it's a tribute to lost lives.\n\n9. **\"Fast Car\" by Tracy Chapman**\n   - A narrative song that tells the story of dreams, hardship, and the longing for a better life.\n\n10. **\"Hurt\" by Johnny Cash (originally by Nine Inch Nails)**\n    - Cash's rendition adds a layer of reflection and remorse, especially poignant given his own life experiences.\n\n11. **\"My Heart Will Go On\" by Celine Dion**\n    - Known as the theme from the movie *Titanic*, it evokes the enduring nature of love amidst tragedy.\n\n12. **\"Yesterday\" by The Beatles**\n    - A classic song about longing for the simplicity of the past and dealing with change.\n\n13. **\"Dancing On My Own\" by Robyn**\n    - While upbeat in tempo, the lyrics convey feelings of loneliness and unrequited love.\n\n14. **\"All I Want\" by Kodaline**\n    - A song about yearning and the pain of separation, often striking a chord with those who've experienced loss.\n\n15. **\"Un-break My Heart\" by Toni Braxton**\n    - A soulful plea for reconciliation after a heartbreaking breakup.\n\nEveryone has different triggers and associations when it comes to music, so while these songs are commonly known to evoke strong emotions, individual experiences may vary. If you're seeking songs that resonate personally with you, reflecting on moments in your life and the music that accompanied them can be a meaningful way to curate your own emotional playlist.",
